 Recently published NICE guidelines recommend using fluid warmers for all infusions of 500mls or more and forced-air warming blankets for all main theatre operations.

 These guidelines have been extrapolated from work done on longer operations.

 Patients whose temperature drops below 36 degrees Centigrade during or after surgery suffer more complications and blood loss than those whose temperature remains above 36 degrees Centigrade.

